This paper deals with the problem of generating private keys, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The concept of effectively concealing the private keys from the remaining terminal is related to cryptography (cs.CR). The problem of characterizing the largest rates can be seen as a capacity region problem, which is a common topic in communication theory (cs.CC). The use of three terminals suggests a possible application in network coding (cs.CE). Finally, the problem of generating private keys can also be seen as a security issue, which is a topic in systems and information security (cs.SI).
